text.__SUMMARY__: Conus alrobini is a species of sea snail, a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Conidae, the cone snails, cone shells or cones.These snails are predatory and venomous. They are capable of "stinging" humans.
text.Description: The length  of the shell attains 105 mm.
text.Distribution: This marine species of cone snail is endemic and occurs off Central Vietnam
text.References: Thach N.N. (2016). Vietnamese new mollusks. Seashells – Land snails – Cephalopods. With 59 new species. 205 pp. Published by the author. page(s): 53
